old beggar woman arrives at a castle during a ball 
and offers the host, a cruel and selfish prince, an enchanted rose in return for shelter from a storm.
 When he refuses the offer, the enchantress reveals her true form and transforms the prince into a beast and his servants into household objects 
She warns the prince that the curse will be broken, only if he can learn to love another and have that person love him in return by the time the last petal of the rose falls
r else he will remain a beast for the rest of his life while his servants become inanimate.
